# Docker

**Always prefer Compose v2** (`docker compose` — space, plugin). Legacy **Compose v1** (`docker-compose` Python 1.29.x) is end-of-life and breaks against current Docker Engine with `KeyError: 'ContainerConfig'` when recreating containers.

```bash
# Prefer v2; fall back only if v2 is not installed
docker compose version || docker-compose version
```

Install the v2 plugin on Debian/Ubuntu if missing: `sudo apt-get install docker-compose-v2` (package name may vary by distro).

- Use `docker compose up --build`, not `docker-compose up --build`, for local dev.
